The paper deals with the problem of loop closure detection in simultaneous localization and mapping (SLAM) using LiDAR sensor data. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as well as computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of a novel global descriptor that combines both intensity and geometry information, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves text processing and natural language understanding, which suggests that it may also be relevant to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
